  *William S. Thoreson, President*    *Robert J. Hartley, Vice President*

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

February 8, 1909

Mr. Charles W. Pemberton

Pemberton & Sons Supply Co.

118 Main Street

Dallas, Texas

Dear Mr. Pemberton,

Thank you for your prompt delivery of the maple and oak lumber we
discussed at our last meeting. Mr. Hartley and I have inspected the
shipment and find the quality to be excellent, well suited to our spring
line of rocking horses and building blocks.

We would like to place an additional order for 400 board feet of
select-grade maple, to be delivered no later than March 1st. As before,
please direct all invoices to my attention at the Commerce Street
office. Mr. Hartley will arrange for warehouse inspection upon arrival.

Business has been strong this quarter, and we anticipate expanding our
catalog this summer. We value the relationship between our firms and
look forward to continued partnership.

Yours truly,

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  William S. Thoreson                 Robert J. Hartley

  William S. Thoreson                 Robert J. Hartley

  *President*                         *Vice President*
